<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
        }
        .error-container {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8d7da 0%, #f5c6cb 100%);
            border: 2px solid #dc3545;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 40px;
            text-align: center;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .error-icon {
            font-size: 64px;
            color: #dc3545;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .error-code {
            font-size: 48px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #dc3545;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .error-details {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 6px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            text-align: left;
        }
        .detail-row {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            margin: 10px 0;
            padding: 8px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        }
        .detail-label {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #495057;
        }
        .detail-value {
            color: #dc3545;
            font-family: monospace;
        }
        .testing-info {
            background: #e7f3ff;
            border: 1px solid #b3d9ff;
            border-radius: 4px;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            text-align: left;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="error-container">
        <div class="error-icon">ðŸ’¥</div>
        <div class="error-code">500</div>
        <h1><%= title %></h1>
        <p>This endpoint always returns an HTTP 500 Internal Server Error for testing error handling and retry logic.</p>
        
        <div class="error-details">
            <h3>Error Details</h3>
            <div class="detail-row">
                <span class="detail-label">Status Code:</span>
                <span class="detail-value">500</span>
            </div>
            <div class="detail-row">
                <span class="detail-label">Error Type:</span>
                <span class="detail-value">Internal Server Error</span>
            </div>
            <div class="detail-row">
                <span class="detail-label">Request ID:</span>
                <span class="detail-value"><%= requestId %></span>
            </div>
            <div class="detail-row">
                <span class="detail-label">Timestamp:</span>
                <span class="detail-value"><%= timestamp %></span>
            </div>
            <div class="detail-row">
                <span class="detail-label">Behavior:</span>
                <span class="detail-value">Always fails</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="testing-info">
            <h4>ðŸ§ª Testing Purpose</h4>
            <p>This endpoint is designed to test:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Error Handling:</strong> How the CLI handles HTTP 500 errors</li>
                <li><strong>Retry Logic:</strong> Whether retry mechanisms work correctly</li>
                <li><strong>Batch Processing:</strong> Error handling in batch operations</li>
                <li><strong>Logging:</strong> Error reporting and logging functionality</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>CLI Testing</h4>
            <p><strong>Expected Behavior:</strong> CLI should report the error and handle it according to configured retry/error policies.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Single conversion: Should fail with error message</li>
                <li>Batch processing: Should continue with other URLs (if configured)</li>
                <li>Retry enabled: Should attempt retries before final failure</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p style="color: #6c757d; font-style: italic; margin-top: 30px;">
            This is a simulated error for testing purposes. The server is functioning normally.
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>